Title: Linking forum posts - classical-HW-002-1-T1.1
Description: The workers will be presented with posts from a forum thread where instructors of a course have replied to student posts. The worker is required to: identify the student post(s) that the instructor’s reply addresses. Instructor's reply post is highlighted
Keywords: tagging, categorization, discussion forum, forum threads, mooc
Input.threadtitle: Quiz due dates
Input.posts:
Also, as far as the quiz attempts go- you can make up to 5 attempts, and considering you do the before the due date, your highest score will be the officially recorded one?  Is this correct?  Are there no penalties for multiple attempts?
Upvotes:
0
Input.inst_post:
Instructor's Post
Hi everyone  TA here. The due date for Quiz 1 is correct and subsequent due dates will be revealed as the quiz is published. Yes, you won't be penalized for multiple attempts, the highest score will be the one recorded. Good advice by Paul Carroll and Jon Casbon (nice to see you again!)

Input.threadtitle: Making sure I do all the quizzes and assignments that are graded.
Input.posts:
I posted this in a previous thread but I think it got overlooked. I just wanted to double check on all the required graded assignments. In the syllabus it says: ' 3 graded online quizzes (week 1, 2, and 4) and 1 final peer-assessed project'. Are these all the official assignments that we need to do associated with this course (i.e. week 3, 5 and 6 don't have any graded quizzes)?  The reason I'm asking is because I missed some assignments in past coursera courses and as a result got a really low final grade. I just want to make sure I don't miss anything that is required. Thanks! 
Upvotes:
0
Input.inst_post:
Instructor's Post
Hi Ivan, Yes that is correct. You must do the 3 quizzes + peer assessment later on.
Instructor's post : Hi Ivan, Yes that is correct. You must do the 3 quizzes + peer assessment later on.

0
